      • menu

        public static int menu(java.util.Scanner kb)
        The menu method prompts the user for a menu choice. This method ensures that the entered choice is within the range of 1 to 5 inclusive.
        Menu choices are:
        1) Enter a new number
        2) Print the number of even/odd/zeros
        3) Print if the number is light or heavy
        4) Print the primes from 2 to the entered number
        5) Quit
        Parameters:
        kb - Representing the Scanner to the keyboard
        Returns:
        int Representing the menu choice, must ensure the number is between 1 and 5 inclusive
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the Scanner is null

      • lightOrHeavy

        public static void lightOrHeavy(int theNum,
                                java.util.Scanner kb)
        The lightOrHeavy method calculates the average of the sum of the digits of number passed in. Take the sum of the digits and divide by the total number of numbers in the number passed in.
        Next generate a random number between 1 and theNumber doubled inclusive. If the average of the sum of digits of the number passed in is greater than the average of the sum of the digitts of the second number than the number is heavy otherwise it is light.
        Parameters:
        theNum - Representing a positive number > 0
        kb - Representing the Scanner to the keyboard
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if theNum is < 1
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the Scanner is null
